Another important question, what's the best way to debug `hublParameters`?

I have an issue with some of the JSON coming from a HubL function on the theme side coming through as escaped JSON, even if I use the json filters available in HubL.

Right now I have to deploy a build with `logWarn()` just to see what's going on with the data, which is not great. I might be missing something on how to work with `hublParameters`?

Just to clarify, I am parsing the JSON on the JS side.
The issue for me is just the debugging method.
So, potential nice to have feature would be debug output in the browser of passed `hublParameters` maybe even entire props shape that exists server side?
Can you provide an example of the hubl function you are using and how you are passing via the `module` tag?
